text_highlighted:
Go to the READ tab of the app and tap your NFC tag under your device.

Then NFC Tools shows you all the technical information of your NFC chip and the data it contains.

NFC Tools is an app which allows you to read, write and program tasks on your NFC tags and other compatible chips.

We recommend using NFC tags compatible with your device (like NTAG21x).
You don't have NFC tags? Don't panic! Here is a list of recommended NFC tags.

Go to the WRITE tab for write data to your NFC tag.

The available records are standard and allow your NFC tag to be readable by everyone, without additional application.

OTHER tab allows you to perform operations on your NFC tag.

You want to copy, format or protect it with a password, it's here.

The TASKS tab allows you to record tasks on your NFC tag. Simply tap your NFC tag and your device will execute the preprogrammed actions.

Warning, this part requires the installation of an additional free app called NFC Tasks. This app has the necessary rights for the proper execution of tasks, and it allows for anyone to run the tasks present on your tag.
Do you enjoy using NFC Tools? If so, please take a moment to leave a review on Google Play. It won't take more than a minute and can help us a lot :)
Welcome to NFC Tools Pro Edition
For using your tasks, you need to install this additional free application
